divs: Sighting Detailsafter an evening at a friens house i exited the front door and looked to my north and noticed a bright very star and looked back again and noticed it moving from north to south. Asked my friend to come to his front yard and observe it. (he is ex military) The light at about my 10 oclock we noticed a smaller light moving much faster and blinking in a slow (3 sec interval) caught up with the larger ball if light and passed it. The smaller blinking light duration was about 40 sec. The larger light at the end of th event slowly got smaller and went out. From the first sight too end of event was about a min.
Summary: Bigger than a star, ball of light ,+ a faster blinking light, below.
